The mayor announced on Monday that Xulu had been sacked for serious misconduct at the power utility. JOHANNESBURG - Johannesburg Mayor Herman Mashaba is warning sacked City Power Managing Director Sicelo Xulu could now face criminal charges.The mayor announced on Monday that Xulu had been sacked for serious misconduct at the power utility.Xulu was first placed on special leave in February during investigations.The mayor says the forensic department is compiling a report which will be handed to law enforcement agencies. We are really concerned with the level of corruption that was left to happen in the City of Johannesburg by the previous administration. It is beyond belief to understand why these matters were not handled in the past. 